questions: Is it something physical/tangible that you can touch or see in the real world?
Is it something that was created/manufactured by humans (man-made)?
Is it a living organism (or was it once alive)?
Is it an animal (as opposed to a plant, fungus, or microorganism)?
Is it a plant (as opposed to fungi or microorganisms)?
Is it a tree (as opposed to a smaller plant like a flower, grass, or shrub)?
Is it an evergreen/coniferous tree (keeps its needles/leaves year-round) as opposed to a deciduous tree (loses its leaves seasonally)?
Is it a tree that produces edible fruits, nuts, or seeds that humans commonly consume?
Does this tree primarily produce fleshy fruits (like apples, peaches, cherries) rather than nuts or seeds?
Is it a tree that primarily grows in temperate climates (as opposed to tropical or subtropical regions)?
Is the fruit of this tree primarily red when ripe (like apples or cherries can be)?
Is the fruit of this tree larger than a golf ball when fully ripe?
